                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable D</hi> 157.) I took the prisoner in the gallery of the theatre—he was drunk—in going to the station he said, "What do you want me for?"—I said "For stealing some silver and a bowl from the Chancellor"—he laid he was there drinking brandy and water, it was a bad job, it could not be helped.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I did not take the bowl, neither was I leaning over near it—I did not go down Hatton-street.</p>
